    <briefdescription>
<para>Decorator that applies a simple moving average (sliding window) filter. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Motor</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Base motor class (must implement <ref refid="classevam_1_1_sliding_window_decor_1ab6308581599cf3e125e2c7a43a9e4ab3" kindref="member">Go(signed short)</ref>) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>N</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Window size (number of values to average). Must be &gt;= 1.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The filter only produces filtered output after the buffer is full. Before that, values pass through unchanged. For N=1, the filter passes values through without any averaging (no effect). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
